1
00:00:03,803 --> 00:00:06,806
The relationship between language and thought.

2
00:00:07,073 --> 00:00:09,376
Human thought is one of the greatest gifts

3
00:00:09,476 --> 00:00:11,311
with which God Almighty has favored him.

4
00:00:11,520 --> 00:00:15,615
Thought is a vast set of mental and cognitive processes

5
00:00:17,217 --> 00:00:19,168
carried out by the human mind,

6
00:00:19,452 --> 00:00:22,800
enabling it to conceptualize the world in which it lives.

7
00:00:25,158 --> 00:00:28,361
Consequently, humans become capable of dealing with it with

8
00:00:28,895 --> 00:00:31,164
with high effectiveness and efficiency.

9
00:00:31,398 --> 00:00:33,199
The relationship between human thought

10
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:34,834
and language is a close one,

11
00:00:35,702 --> 00:00:37,671
as language is the great gateway

12
00:00:37,937 --> 00:00:39,939
through which a person derives knowledge

13
00:00:40,140 --> 00:00:42,375
and science from outside themselves,

14
00:00:44,110 --> 00:00:46,680
and it is also the primary means to reach

15
00:00:46,846 --> 00:00:48,515
the highest levels of comprehension

16
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:51,084
and understanding of the external world

17
00:00:51,785 --> 00:00:52,919
through listening,

18
00:00:53,086 --> 00:00:53,720
 reading,

19
00:00:54,254 --> 00:00:55,121
writing,

20
00:00:55,355 --> 00:00:56,140
speaking,

21
00:00:56,556 --> 00:00:57,424
thinking,

22
00:00:57,657 --> 00:00:58,625
and understanding.

23
00:00:58,858 --> 00:01:00,226
No one can deeply understand

24
00:01:00,326 --> 00:01:01,895
what they read or hear

25
00:01:02,429 --> 00:01:04,064
more than when they read

26
00:01:04,130 --> 00:01:05,532
or hear it in their own language,

27
00:01:09,469 --> 00:01:11,071
nor can they express themselves

28
00:01:11,171 --> 00:01:13,139
 with the utmost clarity and depth,

29
00:01:13,506 --> 00:01:15,108
in speaking and writing,

30
00:01:15,141 --> 00:01:16,643
except in their mother tongue,

31
00:01:16,676 --> 00:01:19,379
because thinking is completely linked to language;

32
00:01:19,979 --> 00:01:21,815
thought relies on language

33
00:01:22,148 --> 00:01:23,883
with its various components

34
00:01:23,983 --> 00:01:26,263
whether in terms of a person's vocabulary,

35
00:01:26,553 --> 00:01:28,488
the system of the language itself,

36
00:01:29,122 --> 00:01:32,072
or the meanings and connotations of its words,

37
00:01:32,692 --> 00:01:35,762
through which humans see and understand the world,

38
00:01:36,329 --> 00:01:38,840
and by which they can also produce

39
00:01:38,860 --> 00:01:40,333
the thoughts they wish to convey

40
00:01:40,533 --> 00:01:41,735
to the outside world.
